-- Egypt expects more than $4bln foreign direct investment this financial yr -min
-- 
-- Tue Jan 28, 2014 03:31AM EST
-- None



CAIRO, Jan 28 (Reuters) - Egypt expects to receive more than $4 billion in foreign direct investment in the fiscal year until the end of June, Investment Minister Osama Saleh said on Tuesday, more than he had previously announced.

"We are targeting four billion (dollars) but expect more," Saleh told reporters at a conference in Cairo.